com.vmware.connectors.common.payloads.response

Class CardAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vmware.connectors.common.payloads.response.CardAction

  • public class CardAction
extends Object
    This class represents a single action that can be taken by the user to whom the containing Card is displayed.

    Instances of this class are unmodifiable once created. The CardAction class cannot be directly constructed; use the CardAction.Builder class to create and populate a CardAction instance.

    Created by Rob Worsnop on 9/13/16.

      • getRequest

        public Map<String,String> getRequest()
        Returns a map of key/value pairs to be submitted to the value of getUrl() using a form. We would expect a template to convert these values to hidden input fields.

        The Map returned by this method is unmodifiable - its contents cannot be changed once the CardAction is created. Use CardAction.Builder.addRequestParam() to add request parameters to the Action.

        Returns:
        the request values

      • getUserInput

        public List<CardActionInputField> getUserInput()
        Returns a list of user input elements to be submitted to the value of getUrl() using a form. We would expect a template to convert these values to input fields, where the id of the field matches the value in the set.

        The List returned by this method is unmodifiable - its contents cannot be changed once the CardAction is created. Use CardAction.Builder.addUserInput() to add user input fields to the Action.

        Returns:
        the user input field IDs, in the order they were added

      • getCompletedLabel

        public String getCompletedLabel()
        Returns the "completed label". This is the text to be displayed to the user on successful completion of the action.
        Returns:
        the completed label
